∗9.42. Let Ω be a countable set and let D be the set of total order relations on Ω for which Ω is order-isomorphic with Q. Does there exist a transitive proper subgroup G of Sym(Ω) which is transitive on D?
P. M. Neumann
∗An affirmative answer is consistent with the ZFC axioms of set theory (S. M. Corson, S. Shelah, Preprint, 2025, https://arxiv.org/abs/2503.12997).
